of subsection (a) do not have any effect on rights of way under subsection (b).","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(4), the words “or his successor in his discretion” are omitted as unnecessary.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the text of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s5"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 5","children":[],"tail":" (last paragraph) is omitted as obsolete. The word “Secretary” is substituted for “the head of the department having jurisdiction over the lands” and “chief officer of the department under whose supervision or control such reservation falls” because the portion of the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1911-03-04"},"text":"March 4, 1911","children":[],"tail":" (ch. 238, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/1253"},"text":"36 Stat. 1253","children":[],"tail":") classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s5"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 5","children":[],"tail":" relates only to System units."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
